). The business case is complete and 'positive' with cost/benefit modeling under the finance director's review for the EMT (Ari Alm, 15 May 2026), but no specific quantified ROI, savings target or cycle-time reduction has been stated on any call or field. Ari flagged the case will be scrutinized because Q1 results were weak ('there will be a lot of hard questions', 15 May 2026), so co-authoring a quantified value narrative with peer CPG benchmarks (Heineken ROI) before the EMT session is the highest-leverage move."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Ari Alm on all four calls (29 Aug 2025, 17 Feb, 15 May, 22 May 2026)", "OpportunityContactRole (PRIMARY, Evaluator)"], "narrative": "Ari Alm (Senior Procurement Manager - ICT & Digital Marketing, ari.alm@anora.com) is a strong, active operational champion engaged consistently across all four calls (Aug 2025 to May 2026). He drove the RFI process, coordinated the business case, introduced Lotta into the evaluation, and is coaching Zycus on exactly what the EMT needs to see (a 5-10 minute benefits-focused video, Heineken example, no UI detail, 15 and 22 May 2026). He has access to the VP Sourcing and the finance director who own the EMT pitch. Strength is strong and active; the gap is that Ari is mid-level and we have no direct relationship above him, so building the upward connection to the VP Sourcing and finance director before the Aug-Sep decision is the champion-development move."}, "competition": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Ari Alm 17 Feb 2026 call", "Competitors__c (null)", "Ari Alm 15 & 22 May 2026 calls"], "narrative": "No competitor has been named on any call, in any Salesforce field (Competitors__c is null), or in any Next_Step or Task. The 17 Feb 2026 call references a 'long list of different partners, your competitors included' receiving the RFI, but Anora deliberately will not disclose the shortlist to keep the process unbiased. All engagement has been cooperative with no pricing objection, feature gap, or reference to a rival's strength, and Ari requested Zycus demo materials for the EMT pitch, signaling Zycus is a serious and well-positioned contender. The named firms in calls (PwC, KPMG, EY, Deloitte) are implementation partners/auditors, not S2P competitors, and must not be treated as such. The wedge is our AI/Merlin differentiation and single-partner end-to-end delivery model (Anora's stated preference, 17 Feb 2026)."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Discovery call 29 Aug 2025", "Lotta 17 Feb 2026 call"], "narrative": "Anora's pain is operational fragmentation and manual-process inefficiency following recent M&A. On the 29 Aug 2025 discovery call they described fragmented procurement across Denmark, Sweden and Norway, manual and labor-intensive tendering, weak master data, and digital tools limited to reporting with no end-to-end automation ('I want to have less touch by people, rather more by machine'). The pain owner is the sourcing function, operationally driven by Ari Alm and Lotta (process harmonization). The Norway ERP migration completed Feb 2026 was a prerequisite, signaling this is a strategic post-integration capability build rather than a discretionary purchase, though buyer confidence is tempered by weak Q1 trading."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Lotta 17 Feb 2026 call", "Ari Alm 17 Feb 2026 call"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics are not yet visible: no MSA, SOW, legal review, InfoSec questionnaire or procurement channel has been discussed on any call and no contract field is populated. Anora completed its ERP consolidation (Norway factory migrated onto unified SAP ECC, confirmed 17 Feb 2026), removing a major integration prerequisite, and prefers a single implementation partner to own delivery end-to-end (17 Feb 2026). The paper process will only activate after EMT approval in Aug-Sep 2026; until then it is genuinely unknown. Visibility would come from confirming the post-approval commercial/legal timeline and the intended procurement and InfoSec route with Ari."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Lotta 17 Feb 2026 call", "Ari Alm 15 May 2026 call", "OpportunityContactRole"], "narrative": "Budget authority is understood at the role level: senior management secured funding for the program (Lotta, 17 Feb 2026: 'we have now the buy in and the support from the senior management, so it is good to go, and we have the funding secured'), and the final cost/benefit approval sits with the relevant stakeholder Team, with the VP of Sourcing presenting alongside the finance director (Ari Alm, 15 May 2026). However neither the VP Sourcing, the finance director, nor any EMT member has ever joined a Zycus call, so we have no direct relationship with the economic decision body. Securing an introduction to the VP Sourcing and finance director through Ari before the Aug-Sep decision is the key access move."}, "decision_process": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Ari Alm 17 Feb 2026 call", "Ari Alm 15 May 2026 call", "Next_Step__c early Jun 2026"], "narrative": "Anora is running a disciplined internal process the buyer laid out on 17 Feb 2026: eRFI to a longlist, evaluation and scoring, business case build, shortlist, a commercial/RFP and contract-negotiation phase, reference calls, then sign-off (targeted originally for Q4 2026). RFI scoring is complete but Anora is withholding feedback until senior management rules on the business case (Ari, 15 May 2026). The program is now formally on hold until Sep 2026 for an EMT cost/benefit decision, with an update promised by end Q3 (Next_Step__c). The approval chain is clear (VP Sourcing + finance director prepare the case, EMT approves), but the process is paused at the funding gate."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Ari Alm 17 Feb 2026 call", "Ari Alm 15 May 2026 call", "AIS_Why__c"], "narrative": "The evaluation is a structured RFI Anora authored themselves, deliberately declining Zycus's generic question template to keep the process unbiased ('we have the same offer from your competitors, and to keep the process non biased, I think it is better that we come up with our own requirements', Ari, 17 Feb 2026). Stated criteria include full S2P suite coverage, hands-on demo/testing of the environment, single-partner end-to-end delivery, references, and a positive business case (17 Feb and 15 May 2026 calls). The RFI was released around week 10 (early Mar 2026) and scoring is finalized (15 May 2026). The AI/Merlin story is acknowledged but not yet a confirmed selection driver (AIS 6, Moderate)."}}}